                    <head>Nicolaus de Lyra, Postillae super Actus Apostolorum, Epistolas Canonicas, Apocalypsin</head>
                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc form="codex">
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>
                                        <locusGrp>
                                            <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                            <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>
                                        </locusGrp>
                                        <material>Parchment</material>
                                        <dimensions type="leaf">
                                            <height quantity="285" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="205" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                    </p>
                                </support>
                                <extent>
                                    <measure type="leftFlyleaves" quantity="0" unit="folios"/>
                                    <measure type="rightFlyleaves" quantity="0" unit="folios"/>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>Modern foliation in pencil. <secFol>declarauit et hoc est quod dicit</secFol>
                                </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1-5(16), 6(18), 7-12(16), 13(18)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/67e6928ff060c60001cbaa6b/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. Parchment guards with text visible on the insde.</p>
                                    <catchwords>Catchwords at the end of each quire. </catchwords>
                                </collation>
                                <condition>
                                    <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and<locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>have text on the verso vaguely visible through the parchment. The flyleaves have detached in the corners where some of the text is visible. The text has left an offprint on the boards.</condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner: National Library book label with current signum; top of page in brown ink by a medieval hand: <quote>Pertinet bernardus hannegren</quote> (?); below, in brown ink by a medieval hand: a table of contents; bottom of page: a glued on fragment from another document with text in Latin.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="unknown">
                                <p>Medieval or early modern binding. Leather over cardboard. 3 double raised bands and endbands. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, four papers labels, three of which are pasted over older labels. From top to bottom: <quote>N. 18</quote>, <quote>56.</quote>, <quote>(155)</quote>; <quote>N<hi rend="super">o</hi> 16. Hic Lyrani commentarius in Epistolas Pauli et Apocalypin</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 156</quote>; <quote>16</quote>; <quote>e 30. 3. 3.</quote>. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, traces of a label on the upper part of the cover. There are also traces of writing in black ink directly on the cover.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="310" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="220" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="65" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather extremley worn. Boards exposed in several places. Holes in covers after corner pieces or bosses and probably also clasps.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName cert="low" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100208">Austria</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1375" notBefore="1325">14th century, middle of</origDate>. The place of origin and dating are tentatively based on the watermark.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Early provenance unknown. On <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> a medieval hand states that the book belongs to one Bernardus Hannegren(?). The manuscript has been at the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> since at least the 17th century. Most of the signa on the spine correspond to older library catalogues. The manuscript is listed in Jaches's catalogue of of 1695 (U 118:10) as <quote>155</quote>, and in the catalogue of 1698 (U 122) as <quote>56</quote>; as <quote>16</quote> in the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e); and as <quote>e. 30. 3. 3.</quote> in Hammarsköld's catalogue of the 19th century (U 133). The signum <quote>18</quote> has not been identified.</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
